snippet.textDisplay:
I like Connor as a fighter, but saying that he has "never been beat" is actually pretty unsportsmanlike and disrespectful against Nate Diaz I think. He should acknowledge that Diaz was the better man in that fight and that he did beat him. If he thinks it doesn't count when you tap out, then why does he do MMA at all? Then maybe he should do kickboxing instead.

P.S Diaz was destroying him in the stand-up, that's why Connor was the one going for the takedown, out of necessity cus he was getting wrecked. So either way, I think Diaz would have knocked him out on the feet if they wouldn't have gone to the ground. Cus Diaz was really lighting him up.
